But to make it simpler, we can use `congr_arg` to get that since `(Ideal.Quotient.lift (ker f) f hfI) ∘ (Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f)) = f`, then applying both sides to `x` gives `(Ideal.Quotient.lift (ker f) f hfI) (Ideal.Quotient.mk (ker f) x) = f x`.

